input: Anne is not kind. Anne is smart. Anne is white. Bob is green. Bob is nice. Fiona is nice. Gary is red. If someone is red and nice then they are rough. If Fiona is red and Fiona is rough then Fiona is kind. Red people are nice. Rough people are nice. If Gary is red and Gary is smart then Gary is white. Kind people are smart. If someone is green and not nice then they are smart. Rough people are kind. If someone is nice and white then they are kind. Question: Gary is white.?
output:
universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Anne : obj
constant Bob : obj
constant Fiona : obj
constant Gary : obj

constant Kind : obj → Prop
constant Smart : obj → Prop
constant White : obj → Prop
constant Green : obj → Prop
constant Red : obj → Prop
constant Nice : obj → Prop
constant Rough : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : ¬ Kind Anne
axiom T2 : Smart Anne
axiom T3 : White Anne
axiom T4 : Green Bob
axiom T5 : Nice Bob
axiom T6 : Nice Fiona
axiom T7 : Red Gary

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Red x ∧ Nice x → Rough x
axiom R2 : Red Fiona ∧ Rough Fiona → Kind Fiona
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Red x → Nice x
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Rough x → Nice x
axiom R5 : Red Gary ∧ Smart Gary → White Gary
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Kind x → Smart x
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Green x ∧ ¬ Nice x → Smart x
axiom R8 : ∀ x : obj, Rough x → Kind x
axiom R9 : ∀ x : obj, Nice x ∧ White x → Kind x

theorem gary_is_white : White Gary :=
begin
  apply R5,
  split,
  exact T7,
  apply R6,
  apply R8,
  apply R1,
  split,
  exact T7,
  apply R3,
  exact T7,
end

-- The answer is True
